#Meta key
Alt-a append
Alt-b  back word
Alt-c change
Alt-e  forward word end
Alt-f  find
Alt-h/j/k/l  move around
Alt-i  insert
Alt-p paste
Alt-s erase
Alt-v  visual
Alt-w  forward word
Alt-u  undo change

Ctrl+c: Cancel the running command or task on the terminal.
Ctrl+d: Logout from the terminal. It is similar to ‘exit‘ command.
Ctrl+z: Pauses running command.
Ctrl+s: Freeze the Cursor.
Ctrl+q: Resume the Cursor.

Ctrl+u: cut left
Ctrl+k: cut right
Ctrl+y: Paste
Ctrl+w: undo insert
Ctrl+-: undo
Ctrl+t: swap one charactor
Ctrl+h: backspace

Ctrl+p: up one line
Ctrl+n: down one line
Ctrl+j: new line
Ctrl+m: enter

Ctrl+l: Clear, Alt-d j enter Normal mode, then Ctrl-l clear screen
Ctrl+r: search
Ctrl+i: completion

!!                 Repeat last command
!<keyword>         Repeat most recent command
!<keyword>:p       print but not excute
!*                 All arguments of the last command
!^                 First arguments of the last command
!$                 Last arguments of the last command
!!:s/linux/bash/   substitut the first occurrence
!<N>               run the N command
!#                 repeat all what you have typed in the entire command line
!#:2               keywords with :nth keyword, 0 is command itself, 1 is first parameter etc
